      "content": "For a free ChatGPT session that is not signed in, there is no official, published “exact” context window size. However, based on OpenAI documentation and community reports:\n\nSigned-in GPT-4 / GPT-4-turbo: typically has 8,192 tokens (some versions up to 128k tokens for pro users).\n\nFree, non-signed-in users are usually on GPT-3.5, which has a context window of roughly 4,096 tokens.\n\nSo on average, for a free session without signing in, you can expect ≈4,000 tokens as the practical context window. This includes both your input and the model’s responses.\n\nIf you want, I can also explain how token count roughly translates into words or characters, which helps estimate when you’re approaching the limit. Do you want me to do that?"
